                <!-- Measuring Impact Start -->
                <section id="measuring" class="container py-5">
                    <div class="text-center mb-5">
                        <h2 class="display-5 fw-bold">Measuring Impact</h2>
                        <p>At Building Lives for Sustainable Project (BLSP), impact is at the heart of everything
                            we do. We measure success not only by the number of farmers we reach, but by the
                            real, lasting transformation in productivity, incomes, resilience, and community
                            well-being. Our Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability, and Learning (MEAL)
                            approach ensures that every program we implement delivers meaningful change and
                            contributes to sustainable development. </p>
                        <p> Our impact measurement system is designed to be data-driven, inclusive, and
                            transparent, enabling us to track progress, improve program quality, and
                            demonstrate results to our partners, donors, and communities.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="row g-4">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <h5>1. Farmer Productivity & Yield Improvement</h5>
                            <p>We evaluate how our training, technologies, and farming innovations increase farmers’
                                production capacity.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Percentage increase in crop yield per acre</li>
                                <li>Adoption rate of climate-smart and digital farming practices</li>
                                <li>Reduction in post-harvest losses</li>
                                <li>Increased crop quality and consistency</li>
                            </ul>
                            <hr>
                            <h5>3. Food Security & Nutrition Levels</h5>
                            <p>We track how our initiatives strengthen access to nutritious and stable food supplies.
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Reduction in hunger periods and food shortages</li>
                                <li>Increased household consumption of nutritious foods</li>
                                <li>Grain banks, kitchen gardens, and improved seeds</li>
                                <li>Improvement in child and maternal nutrition outcomes</li>
                            </ul>
                            <hr>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <h5>2. Income Growth & Economic Empowerment</h5>
                            <p>We assess how BLSP programs improve household income and economic stability.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Increase in farmer earnings from produce sales</li>
                                <li>Access to new markets and value chains</li>
                                <li>Financial literacy and cooperative savings growth</li>
                                <li>Farmers transitioning to formal agri-business operations</li>
                            </ul>
                            <hr>
                            <h5>4. Technology Adoption & Innovation Uptake</h5>
                            <p>We measure the impact of modern agricultural technologies introduced to farmers.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Use of solar irrigation, drones, and digital tools</li>
                                <li>Cost savings from energy and water efficiency</li>
                                <li>Youth participation in agri-tech innovations</li>
                                <li>Improved pest/disease detection and monitoring</li>
                            </ul>
                            <hr>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <h5>5. Cooperative Strength & Community Empowerment</h5>
                            <p>We evaluate how organized farmer groups drive economic and social advancement.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Number of active cooperatives established or strengthened</li>
                                <li>Improved cooperative governance and financial management</li>
                                <li>Access to credit, subsidies, and formal markets</li>
                                <li>Collective bargaining gains (better prices, lower input costs)</li>
                                </li>

                            </ul>
                            <hr>

                            <h5>7. Value Addition, Market Access & Agribusiness Growth</h5>
                            <p>We measure how farmers generate higher earnings through processing, packaging,
                                and direct marketing.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Number of farmers trained in agribusiness management
                                <li>Volume and value of processed products (flour, juice, dried fruits etc.)</li>
                                <li>Market linkages facilitated: buyers, processors, exporters</li>
                                <li>Increase in market prices and sales volumes</li>

                            </ul>
                            <hr>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <h5>6. Environmental Sustainability & Climate Resilience</h5>
                            <p>BLSP tracks how community-led environmental actions contribute to long-term
                                resilience.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Number of trees planted and agroforestry systems established</li>
                                <li>Soil health and biodiversity improvements</li>
                                <li>Households using renewable energy and eco-friendly farming</li>
                                <li>Reduction in carbon footprint and increased participation in carbon markets</li>
                            </ul>
                            <hr>

                            <h5>8. Community-Level Outcomes</h5>
                            <p>Beyond individual farmers, we evaluate how entire communities benefit from BLSP
                                programs</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Employment generated through green jobs, agri-tech, processing and
                                    cooperatives</li>
                                <li>Strengthened local economies and reduced rural poverty</li>
                                <li>Increased resilience to droughts, climate shocks, and economic disruptions</li>
                                <li>Improved household well-being: education, health, and food stability</li>

                            </ul>
                            <hr>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </section>
